==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Old English language|Old English]] [[sesoun]], [[w:French language|French]] [[saison]], (meaning properly, the sowing time), from [[w:Latin|Latin]] [[satio]] (meaning a sowing, a [[plant]]ing), from [[serere]], [[satum]], (to sow, plant); akin to English [[sow]], (meaning to scatter, as seed).

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-season.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːzən|-iːzən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Each of the four divisions of a [[year]]: [[spring]], [[summer]], [[autumn]] and [[winter]].
# A part of a year when something particular happens: ''[[mating]] season'', ''[[rainy]] season'', ''[[football]] season''.
# {{obsolete}} That which gives [[relish]].
#: ''You lack the season of all natures, sleep.'' [[w:Shakespeare|Shakespeare]]
# {{cricket}} the [[period]] over which a [[series]] of [[test match]]es are played

